25/06/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic met with his Norwegian counterpart, Kristin Krohn Devold, on Thursday (24 June). Afterwards, Roncevic said he had received Devold's assurances that Norway would support Croatia on its road to NATO membership and would share its experiences in military reform. The two officials agreed on future co-operation between their ministries in establishing a Croatian Coast Guard, conducting defence reforms and participating in peacekeeping missions. (HINA, HRT - 24/06/04)
